A biological simulation tracks bacteria growth that triples each cycle. Complete the missing part of the loop to correctly model the growth until the population exceeds 100.

```cpp
#include 
using namespace std;

int main() {
    // Start with 1 bacterium
    for (int population = 1; population <= 100; __) {  // Complete the loop
        cout << population << " ";
    }
    return 0;
}
```

 **Expected Output:**
```default
1 3 9 27 81
```

